22/11/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Local media are reporting on Monday (22 November) that the government is considering a revision of its immigration policy in response to new statistical data suggesting nearly half of the immigrants living in the country are there illegally.
Citing interior ministry sources, the media reports say that between 900,000 and 1.2 million immigrants reside in Greece and around 400,000 of them lack legal papers.
(Kathimerini - 22/11/04)
